{{Infobox museum | name = Belarusian Nature and Environment Museum | native_name = Музей прыроды і экалогіі Рэспублікі Беларусь | native_name_lang = be | image = Belarus-Minsk-National museum of history and culture of Belarus-Entrance.jpg | imagesize = 200 | caption = Facade of the [[Belarusian National History and Culture Museum]], where the museum is located | alt = | map_type = Belarus | map_caption = | map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|53.896789|27.555517|display=inline}} | established = July 25, 1983 | dissolved = | location = Minsk | type = | collection = | visitors = | director = | president = | curator = | publictransit = | network = | website = https://web.archive.org/web/20110502002512/http://mus-eco.com/ }} '''The Museum of Nature and Environment of the Republic of Belarus''' is a [[museum]] in [[Minsk]], [[Belarus]], founded in 1991 at [[Minsk]] on the basis of the nature of [[Belarusian National History and Culture Museum]]. There are more than 40 thousand exhibits inside an exposition area of 350 m². In the 6 thematic rooms (mineralogical, fenalagichny, nature, river, lake, forest) exhibits tell about the natural riches of the evolution of flora and fauna from antiquity to the present day. Carrying out research work to assess the current state of nature, it creates a database (the collection of flora, fauna, mineralogy, paleontology) and promotes environmental knowledge.
