{{Infobox recurring event | name = Sarasvati Pushkaram | native_name = | native_name_lang = | logo = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_size = 100px | image = File:Gita Mandir on Triveni Ghat near Somnath Temple Gujrat.jpg | image_size = 200px | alt = | caption = Triveni Ghat in Somanth is the confluence of three holy rivers namely Kapil, Hiran and a mystical River Saraswathy. | status = Active | genre = [[Hindu festivals]] | begins = | ends = | frequency = every 12 years | venue = [[Triveni Sangam]] | location = [[Prayag]], [[Uttar Pradesh]] | coordinates = | country = [[India]] | first = | founder_name = | last = May 31, 2013 | prev = | next = May 15 - 26, 2025 | participants = | attendance = | capacity = | area = [[North India]] | budget = | activity = Holy river dip | leader_name = | patron = | organised = <!-- "organized=" also works --> | people = | member = | website = | footnotes = }} '''Sarasvati Pushkaram''' is a festival of [[Sarasvati River|River Sarasvati]] normally occurs once in 12 years. Saraswati River is considered as the 'Antarvahini' (invisible river) which flows at Triveni Sangam. This [[Pushkaram]] is observed for a period of 12 days from the time of entry of [[Jupiter]] into ''Mithuna'' rasi ([[Gemini (astrology)|Gemini]]).<ref>{{cite book |author=Roshen Dalal |title=Hinduism: An Alphabetical Guide |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zrk0AwAAQBAJ&pg=PT921 |date=18 April 2014 |publisher=Penguin Books Limited |isbn=978-81-8475-277-9 |pages=921–}}</ref>
